label("$X$",(0,0),NW);
[/asy] Since $\angle BXC=70^\circ,$ then $\angle AXC = 180^\circ - \angle BXC = 110^\circ.$

Since $\angle AXC = 110^\circ,$ then $\angle DXA = 180^\circ - \angle AXC = 70^\circ.$

Therefore, $x=\boxed{70}.$

(Alternatively, we could note that when two lines intersect, the vertically opposite angles are equal so $\angle DXA=\angle BXC =70^\circ.$)

